nodes.bodyText: We actually shouldn't return null if it's a DrugOrder. I'd just handle it as usual anyways.
Please don't use the org.openmrs.api.OrderService here. Instead, create a FhirOrderDao to get the order from the database. I don't want to depend on the OpenMRS Service API if we can avoid it.
We should not being doing this. Let the dateCreated (and dateChanged) fields get updated by the system, not by our code.
What happens if there is no effectiveDateTimeType set for this resource? We should actually have a translator here that can handle (at least) effectiveDateTime and effectiveInstant.
This should still be "ServiceRequest" since "Order" isn't a valid FHIR object type.

In this method, it may make sense to differentiate DrugOrders, but in that case have them return a reference to a "MedicationRequest". However, that only makes sense once the MedicationRequest resource is created.
Again, reference should be to a ServiceRequest, not an Order
In addition to DateTimeType we should also support InstantType here, which is very similar to DateTimeType, but represents a slightly more precise type.
